{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17650918","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17650918"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:17:24+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:17:24+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18421"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18421","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18421"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11139"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74542"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11139","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11139"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18421"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60033"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"12"},{"type":"tags","id":"45"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"2821"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"11268"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25814"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25819"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74542","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74542"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA muscle biopsy for a patient confirms the diagnosis of inclusion body myositis.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following treatments is most likely to benefit this patient?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Glucocorticoids","Immunosuppressive therapy","Physiotherapy","Intravenous immunoglobulin","Plasmapheresis"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPhysiotherapy\u003C/strong\u003E is the most beneficial treatment for patients with inclusion body myositis (IBM). It focuses on maintaining muscle strength and function, as well as improving mobility and quality of life. IBM is a chronic, progressive muscle disorder that primarily affects older adults, and it is typically resistant to immunosuppressive therapies.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGlucocorticoids\u003C/strong\u003E are not effective in treating IBM, as the condition does not respond well to these or other immunosuppressive medications. While glucocorticoids are used in other inflammatory myopathies, they do not alter the course of IBM.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImmunosuppressive therapy\u003C/strong\u003E is generally ineffective in IBM. Unlike other inflammatory myopathies, IBM does not respond to treatments that target the immune system.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntravenous immunoglobulin\u003C/strong\u003E has been tried in IBM, but studies have not shown significant benefit in altering the disease course or improving muscle strength.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPlasmapheresis\u003C/strong\u003E is not a standard treatment for IBM and has not been shown to be effective in managing the condition. It is more commonly used in other autoimmune disorders where removal of circulating antibodies is beneficial.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Inclusion body myositis (IBM) is typically resistant to immunosuppressive therapies, including glucocorticoids.","Physiotherapy is often the mainstay of management in IBM to maintain muscle function and mobility.","IBM is a progressive muscle disorder that primarily affects older adults."],"references":["Patton, K. T., \u0026 Thibodeau, G. A. (2018). Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book: Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Hutson, M., \u0026 Ward, A. (Eds.). (2015). Oxford textbook of musculoskeletal medicine. Oxford University Press","Longo, U. G., \u0026 Denaro, V. (Eds.). (2023). Textbook of musculoskeletal disorders. Springer Nature","Hughes, S. H. (2022). The Musculoskeletal System: The Musculoskeletal System-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Frontera WR, Ochala J. Skeletal muscle: a brief review of structure and function. Calcif Tissue Int. 2015 Mar;96(3):183-95. doi: 10.1007/s00223-014-9915-y. Epub 2014 Oct 8. PMID: 25294644","Morrison BM. Neuromuscular Diseases. Semin Neurol. 2016 Oct;36(5):409-418. doi: 10.1055/s-0036-1586263. Epub 2016 Sep 23. PMID: 27704495","Skolka MP, Naddaf E. Exploring challenges in the management and treatment of inclusion body myositis. Curr Opin Rheumatol. 2023 Nov 1;35(6):404-413. doi: 10.1097/BOR.0000000000000958. Epub 2023 Jul 25. PMID: 37503813; PMCID: PMC10552844."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60033"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18421"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60033","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60033"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-25T06:11:28+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-25T06:12:07+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11139"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74542"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"7","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/7"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udde0","name":"Neurology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"12","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/12"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc4b","name":"Rheumatology","s